00:09:30,341 --> 00:09:32,809
- WOMAN: You know, I kind of liked...
- It's Daniel.

247
00:09:33,560 --> 00:09:35,685
Hold on, hold on.

248
00:09:35,710 --> 00:09:38,057
We have one more. Kevin Pearson.

249
00:09:38,097 --> 00:09:40,510
Sorry. I know, I know. I'm
sorry. I'm sorry I'm late.

250
00:09:40,535 --> 00:09:42,614
It's just, you know, I tried
to take the subway, right,

251
00:09:42,638 --> 00:09:43,949
and then walk, like a New Yorker.

252
00:09:43,973 --> 00:09:46,140
Uh, Ron Shiller.

253
00:09:46,175 --> 00:09:48,076
This is Sloane Sandberg.

254
00:09:48,110 --> 00:09:50,778
- You're the, uh, screenwriter.
- Playwright.

255
00:09:50,813 --> 00:09:53,432
Well, you know, I mean,
you gotta start somewhere.

256
00:09:53,457 --> 00:09:57,239
Um, you'll be reading with Miss
Maine today, if that's okay.

257
00:09:57,271 --> 00:09:59,639
Yeah, no, whatever you got,
you know. Miss Maine, Miss Iowa.

258
00:09:59,674 --> 00:10:01,575
I judged, uh, Miss USA for Trump once,

259
00:10:01,609 --> 00:10:03,410
so we may have actually met before.

260
00:10:03,444 --> 00:10:05,979
Miss Maine is Olivia Maine.

261
00:10:06,466 --> 00:10:08,201
Tony nominee.

262
00:10:08,341 --> 00:10:10,751
SHILLER: She plays Jessica.

263
00:10:10,785 --> 00:10:13,878
Of course. Hi. Good to meet you.

264
00:10:16,591 --> 00:10:18,558
Uh, well, before we
start, I just wanted to...

265
00:10:18,593 --> 00:10:20,550
I want to get something off my chest.

266
00:10:20,575 --> 00:10:22,106
I do understand the
perception, you know.

267
00:10:22,130 --> 00:10:23,607
These L.A. actors, they
come out here, right?

268
00:10:23,631 --> 00:10:26,066
They do their little
quick stint in theater

269
00:10:26,100 --> 00:10:27,244
just to feel better about themselves.

270
00:10:27,268 --> 00:10:30,103
That's not why I'm here, okay?
I'm here for the right reasons.

271
00:10:32,173 --> 00:10:34,775
Let's get this over with, shall we?

272
00:10:35,539 --> 00:10:37,974
[sniffles, clears throat]

273
00:10:46,527 --> 00:10:47,821
Did you want me to start?

274
00:10:47,855 --> 00:10:49,689
Yes, I thought it
would be good, if, uh...

275
00:10:49,724 --> 00:10:52,581
you speak, then I speak, then
you speak, and we all go home.

276
00:10:52,606 --> 00:10:54,795
Does that work for you?

277
00:10:54,829 --> 00:10:56,329
Yeah. That's great...

278
00:10:58,353 --> 00:11:00,187
[clears throat]

279
00:11:03,905 --> 00:11:06,305
My recollection's hazy,
actually, it was a long day.

280
00:11:06,330 --> 00:11:09,810
Not for me. Mine was over
before 9:00 in the morning.

281
00:11:09,844 --> 00:11:11,912
[whispering]: That's
really good... accent.

282
00:11:11,953 --> 00:11:13,754
- What?
- The American accent.

283
00:11:13,781 --> 00:11:15,081
What?

284
00:11:15,979 --> 00:11:18,351
I just... diving...
diving right back in. Uh...

285
00:11:18,386 --> 00:11:20,387
[flipping pages]

286
00:11:21,989 --> 00:11:24,157
It say, uh... it says
"I lay," uh, I don't...

287
00:11:24,192 --> 00:11:25,893
Let me just say... I don't
need to say it. It says...

288
00:11:25,917 --> 00:11:27,217
I'll just say it.

289
00:11:27,283 --> 00:11:28,962
I lay...

290
00:11:29,184 --> 00:11:31,085
Just keep going.

291
00:11:31,121 --> 00:11:33,088
[chuckles softly] This is...

292
00:11:33,123 --> 00:11:34,957
I'll get it. [sniffles]

293
00:11:34,991 --> 00:11:37,306
I lay on the dock all night,

294
00:11:37,331 --> 00:11:39,260
and part of the next morning.

295
00:11:39,296 --> 00:11:40,876
And I don't feel a thing.

296
00:11:43,079 --> 00:11:44,595
Let me take that again.

297
00:11:44,923 --> 00:11:46,935
KEVIN: Oh, my gosh... oh, my gosh.

298
00:11:46,970 --> 00:11:49,605
Okay. Baby say what... [chuckles]

299
00:11:49,639 --> 00:11:53,375
Okay. I-I lay... Let me get into it.

300
00:11:53,410 --> 00:11:56,420
I lay on the dock all night
and part of the next morning.

301
00:11:56,445 --> 00:11:58,404
And I don't feel a thing.

302
00:11:58,429 --> 00:12:02,017
The bug bites, the sunburn. Nothin'.

303
00:12:02,052 --> 00:12:04,420
It's like when we used to
go fishing. You remember?

304
00:12:11,020 --> 00:12:12,248
- I never fished...
- Do you have the next...

305
00:12:12,272 --> 00:12:13,638
- What the hell?
- Sorry.

306
00:12:14,286 --> 00:12:15,726
You weren't talking, so I thought...

307
00:12:16,404 --> 00:12:18,177
- It's called a pause.
- Right.

308
00:12:21,316 --> 00:12:22,895
Sorry. It doesn't say
pause on my script...

309
00:12:22,919 --> 00:12:25,805
Well, it doesn't say suck,
either, yet here we are.

310
00:12:28,599 --> 00:12:30,299
RANDALL: You know your size?

311
00:12:30,334 --> 00:12:31,934
Always tended toward the slim.

312
00:12:31,969 --> 00:12:34,317
I don't see that changing
much at this point.

313
00:12:39,199 --> 00:12:40,392
Try these.

314
00:12:40,417 --> 00:12:42,078
Afterwards, we'll swing by the pharmacy,

315
00:12:42,112 --> 00:12:44,914
get those medications that
the doctor wrote for you.

316
00:12:44,948 --> 00:12:46,749
Sounds like a plan.

317
00:12:46,783 --> 00:12:49,085
Ugh! $100?

318
00:12:49,119 --> 00:12:51,120
It's what they cost.

319
00:12:51,154 --> 00:12:54,357
I'm paying, just take the pants.

320
00:13:01,740 --> 00:13:03,833
So are we gonna talk about it or not?

321
00:13:03,867 --> 00:13:05,167
Talk about what?

322
00:13:05,202 --> 00:13:07,709
Ha. About what. Uh, this morning.

323
00:13:07,734 --> 00:13:11,574
Or are you content to stand in
silent judgment with that face?

324
00:13:11,608 --> 00:13:12,686
It's just my face.

325
00:13:12,711 --> 00:13:15,745
No, you didn't like
me apologizing for you.

326
00:13:15,779 --> 00:13:17,139
I get it.

327
00:13:17,164 --> 00:13:19,154
Would you have been happier
if I made a big scene?

328
00:13:19,186 --> 00:13:20,720
You know, got up in Tony's face,

329
00:13:20,745 --> 00:13:23,319
had the cops roll up
and turn the hoses on us?

330
00:13:23,353 --> 00:13:24,752
It's the Cosgroves.

331
00:13:24,777 --> 00:13:27,944
He runs an insurance
agency, she collects owls.

332
00:13:27,968 --> 00:13:30,437
History would not have
memorialized our stand.

333
00:13:30,468 --> 00:13:31,779
You ever had a hose turned on you?

334
00:13:31,803 --> 00:13:33,280
Can't say that I have, I'm very sorry.

335
00:13:33,304 --> 00:13:35,439
Don't be. It hurts.

336
00:13:35,473 --> 00:13:37,107
And there's that face.

337
00:13:37,141 --> 00:13:39,142
Only face I got. Look,
I could use some socks...

338
00:13:39,177 --> 00:13:41,411
No, the face. The one
that says I have a scar

339
00:13:41,446 --> 00:13:43,480
on my arm from integrating schools.

340
00:13:43,514 --> 00:13:46,596
And probably blisters on your
feet from marching for freedom,

341
00:13:46,631 --> 00:13:49,159
but me, because I grew
up in a white house,

342
00:13:49,184 --> 00:13:51,520
you think I don't live
in a black man's world.

343
00:13:51,614 --> 00:13:52,923
Oh, you know the one.

344
00:13:52,957 --> 00:13:55,425
The one where that salesman
there has been eyeballing us

345
00:13:55,460 --> 00:13:57,661
ever since we came in here.
Or where that security guard

346
00:13:57,695 --> 00:14:00,341
has moved just a little off his
mark so he can keep us in his sight.

347
00:14:00,365 --> 00:14:01,932
And where they'll definitely ask

348
00:14:01,966 --> 00:14:04,167
for an ID with my credit
card when I go to pay,

349
00:14:04,202 --> 00:14:06,536
even though they haven't
asked for anybody else's.

350
00:14:06,571 --> 00:14:11,408
Plus a million things every day that
I have to <i>choose</i> to let go,

351
00:14:11,442 --> 00:14:15,112
just so I'm not pissed off all the time.

352
00:14:15,146 --> 00:14:17,247
Like I did on the street this morning.

353
00:14:17,281 --> 00:14:20,283
Like I have done every day of my life.

354
00:14:22,787 --> 00:14:25,422
Now try on the damn slim
cut flat front chinos.

355
00:14:25,433 --> 00:14:28,669
I think they'll look nice on you.

356
00:14:33,343 --> 00:14:34,435
- KEVIN: Randall!
- Yeah?

357
00:14:34,461 --> 00:14:35,928
Watch!

358
00:14:35,962 --> 00:14:38,631
[chuckling]: Cool! Cool!

359
00:14:38,665 --> 00:14:41,267
Dad, watch! Dad!

360
00:14:41,301 --> 00:14:42,812
- Where's the other one?
- I'm looking.

361
00:14:42,836 --> 00:14:46,051
Man, you take your eyes off one for a
second, you lose track of the others.

362
00:14:46,076 --> 00:14:48,808
That's because there are more
of them than there are of us.

363
00:14:48,842 --> 00:14:51,143
- Always will be.
- What? Oh.

364
00:14:51,178 --> 00:14:52,511
Talking about the kids.

365
00:14:52,546 --> 00:14:54,980
Yep. It's a war. They got the numbers.

366
00:14:55,015 --> 00:14:56,959
- KEVIN: Dad! Dad!
- We were beat before we started.

367
00:14:56,983 --> 00:14:58,517
- Watch!
- There she is.

368
00:14:58,552 --> 00:14:59,785
Hi. Hey, guys.

369
00:14:59,820 --> 00:15:01,120
You want to play mermaids?

370
00:15:01,154 --> 00:15:02,855
This is from all of us.

371
00:15:06,660 --> 00:15:07,927
KEVIN: Dad!

372
00:15:07,961 --> 00:15:10,329
- Dad! Daddy! Dad!
- Yep.

373
00:15:10,363 --> 00:15:13,098
- Dad, watch me!
- Yeah. I see you, pal!

374
00:15:13,670 --> 00:15:16,669
Do you remember the first time
he said "Dad"? How happy I was?

375
00:15:16,703 --> 00:15:18,137
Now where's Randall?

376
00:15:18,811 --> 00:15:22,174
- How about that time? Did you see?
- Hey, Kev. Where's your brother?

377
00:15:22,209 --> 00:15:23,509
I don't know!

378
00:15:23,543 --> 00:15:25,945
- Jack...
- You take land, I'll take sea.

379
00:15:25,979 --> 00:15:28,360
KEVIN: Dad! Watch!

380
00:15:28,385 --> 00:15:29,595
REBECCA: Kevin.

381
00:15:29,620 --> 00:15:31,951
You were supposed to watch each other!

382
00:15:32,548 --> 00:15:34,119
REBECCA: Randall!

383
00:15:34,329 --> 00:15:35,985
Randall!

384
00:15:40,657 --> 00:15:43,523
KEVIN: <i>Aw, Kate it was the worst
audition in the history of the world.</i>

385
00:15:43,548 --> 00:15:45,018
Okay? I mean, that
woman made me so nervous,

386
00:15:45,042 --> 00:15:47,704
I started doing an English accent
in the middle of it for no reason!

387
00:15:47,728 --> 00:15:49,729
Okay, I'm sure it wasn't <i>that bad.</i>

388
00:15:49,764 --> 00:15:51,758
Maybe that's the problem. You
know? I wanted it too much.

389
00:15:51,782 --> 00:15:53,010
Hey! It's the Man-ny!

390
00:15:53,043 --> 00:15:54,920
Hey Man-ny! How's it going? [squeals]

391
00:15:54,945 --> 00:15:57,748
Yeah. Listen. Could you please fly
out here? I really need you right now.

392
00:15:57,772 --> 00:16:00,000
You'll be fine, you just...

393
00:16:00,025 --> 00:16:02,342
What? I'm just what? Where'd you go?

394
00:16:02,376 --> 00:16:03,910
Nowhere. I'm here. I'm shopping.

395
00:16:03,945 --> 00:16:05,512
- I'm lost.
- KATE: You're not lost.

396
00:16:05,546 --> 00:16:08,112
It's just all new. It's just new.

397
00:16:08,137 --> 00:16:10,150
No... I mean I'm actually lost,

398
00:16:10,184 --> 00:16:12,485
I have no idea where the
hell I'm at. I got to go.

399
00:16:12,520 --> 00:16:13,820
- Oh!
- Ow!

400
00:16:13,855 --> 00:16:15,856
Sorry. Oh.

401
00:16:16,881 --> 00:16:19,254
[sighs]
- Hey, uh...

402
00:16:19,358 --> 00:16:22,356
that whole thing back there, just so
you know. I'm not actually bad, okay?

403
00:16:22,381 --> 00:16:24,064
- Okay. Duly noted.
- Okay.

404
00:16:24,098 --> 00:16:25,342
Okay. Just wanted to get that out there.

405
00:16:25,366 --> 00:16:27,000
Well, out there it is.

406
00:16:27,034 --> 00:16:29,035
Although you weren't super helpful.

407
00:16:32,707 --> 00:16:34,541
You want to get a drink?

408
00:16:35,075 --> 00:16:36,176
What, like, now?

409
00:16:36,210 --> 00:16:38,678
Yeah. Now. Come on,

410
00:16:38,841 --> 00:16:40,580
- L.A.
- What? Yeah.

411
00:16:40,615 --> 00:16:42,682
♪

412
00:16:42,717 --> 00:16:45,685
[indistinct chatter]

413
00:16:47,210 --> 00:16:48,955
TESS: Mom, the play's about to start!

414
00:16:48,990 --> 00:16:51,435
All right, Tess. Hurry up. Go get
your dress on. Get her her shoes.

415
00:16:51,459 --> 00:16:52,603
- Hurry, hurry, hurry.
- Break a leg.

416
00:16:52,627 --> 00:16:54,928
Come on... [chuckles]

417
00:16:54,962 --> 00:16:57,287
Wow, this is a nice place.

418
00:16:57,312 --> 00:16:59,235
Yeah. Public schools
in this area are good,

419
00:16:59,271 --> 00:17:00,800
it's why we moved here.

420
00:17:00,835 --> 00:17:02,695
- Even better than private.
- Mm-hmm.

421
00:17:02,729 --> 00:17:04,337
You know, the parents are real involved.

422
00:17:04,362 --> 00:17:06,706
- Mm-hmm.
- You know, Beth's on the board.

423
00:17:06,741 --> 00:17:08,942
Real involved.

424
00:17:10,211 --> 00:17:11,411
They got a farm.

425
00:17:11,445 --> 00:17:13,580
- Really?
- Yeah. Out back.

426
00:17:13,614 --> 00:17:16,161
Kids learn about the
land. Grow their own food.

427
00:17:16,186 --> 00:17:17,997
Thank you.

428
00:17:18,482 --> 00:17:20,661
They got, uh, chickens.

429
00:17:21,489 --> 00:17:23,423
They got a goat.

430
00:17:24,926 --> 00:17:29,129
♪ Wanna take it down,
gonna do my thing ♪

431
00:17:29,163 --> 00:17:31,898
♪ Gonna do my thing ♪

432
00:17:31,933 --> 00:17:34,734
♪ Gonna do my thing ♪

