00:17:34,769 --> 00:17:36,102
♪ Gonna do my thing ♪

434
00:17:36,841 --> 00:17:37,980
Hi.

435
00:17:38,325 --> 00:17:39,857
Can I help you find something?

436
00:17:39,882 --> 00:17:40,882
No.

437
00:17:40,907 --> 00:17:43,276
Oh! You're here about the job.

438
00:17:44,278 --> 00:17:46,590
- Hmm?
- You know. The job? [chuckles]

439
00:17:46,614 --> 00:17:48,263
- Y-yeah.
- Great!

440
00:17:48,288 --> 00:17:49,655
♪ I'm unstoppable ♪

441
00:17:49,680 --> 00:17:52,349
Let's go over here so we can talk.

442
00:17:53,272 --> 00:17:55,907
♪ It's time to hit the road again. ♪

443
00:17:56,934 --> 00:17:58,214
Randall?

444
00:18:00,051 --> 00:18:01,488
Randall?

445
00:18:01,895 --> 00:18:04,183
Hey, Kate. Have you seen Randall?

446
00:18:04,211 --> 00:18:06,488
[sighs] Randall!

447
00:18:06,566 --> 00:18:08,785
_

448
00:18:09,960 --> 00:18:11,961
♪

449
00:18:21,941 --> 00:18:23,942
Randall?

450
00:18:24,358 --> 00:18:25,959
Randall...

451
00:18:27,901 --> 00:18:29,581
Randall! Hello!

452
00:18:29,615 --> 00:18:30,699
Did you not hear me calling you?

453
00:18:30,723 --> 00:18:32,566
- Hey, what are you doing over here?
- Oh, no, no, no...

454
00:18:32,590 --> 00:18:34,550
- I've been...
- It's okay. I'm watching him.

455
00:18:34,578 --> 00:18:36,365
Okay, it's... I-I have
him now. I'm sorry,

456
00:18:36,399 --> 00:18:38,444
I'm his mother. I was a
little panicked. I'm Rebecca.

457
00:18:38,468 --> 00:18:39,702
Oh, we know who you are.

458
00:18:39,736 --> 00:18:41,036
You do?

459
00:18:41,071 --> 00:18:43,238
Oh yes. When a white
family has a black child

460
00:18:43,273 --> 00:18:45,709
and they don't introduce
themselves to any of us,

461
00:18:45,864 --> 00:18:47,765
we tend to take notice.

462
00:18:48,945 --> 00:18:51,547
Well. Thank you for watching him,

463
00:18:51,581 --> 00:18:53,749
He's just not supposed to be over here.

464
00:18:55,351 --> 00:18:57,786
Not... "over here" like that.

465
00:18:57,821 --> 00:19:00,353
There's nothing wrong with over here.

466
00:19:01,526 --> 00:19:03,332
I just mean that I want him

467
00:19:03,356 --> 00:19:05,800
where we can see him. Where
we're sitting. In front of us.

468
00:19:07,026 --> 00:19:09,839
Thank you. It was very nice to meet
you. Randall, come on. Let's go.

469
00:19:09,864 --> 00:19:12,234
Come on. Thank you.

470
00:19:14,604 --> 00:19:17,873
Actually, you stay right here.

471
00:19:17,907 --> 00:19:21,043
That's my son, and I'm his mother.

472
00:19:21,077 --> 00:19:23,422
And I don't know if you have some
sort of problem with that arrangement,

473
00:19:23,446 --> 00:19:24,947
but also, I don't really care.

474
00:19:24,972 --> 00:19:26,647
Thank you very much for watching my son.

475
00:19:26,672 --> 00:19:28,116
But I have him now.

476
00:19:28,141 --> 00:19:29,952
- Okay.
- Okay.

477
00:19:29,986 --> 00:19:32,287
You need to get the
child a proper haircut.

478
00:19:33,066 --> 00:19:35,334
The razor bumps on his neck.

479
00:19:35,368 --> 00:19:38,103
You need a barber who
knows how to cut black hair.

480
00:19:40,073 --> 00:19:41,740
Come on.

481
00:19:41,774 --> 00:19:44,028
Hey, I told you to stay
with your brother. Didn't I?

482
00:19:44,053 --> 00:19:45,877
Sorry.

483
00:19:45,912 --> 00:19:50,048
Is this the real reason you wanted to
come to this pool and not the other?

484
00:19:50,435 --> 00:19:53,885
- Come on.
- [classical music playing]

485
00:20:09,612 --> 00:20:11,198
So beautiful.

486
00:20:11,223 --> 00:20:14,080
BOY: Ho, there. Who
might you be, fair maid?

487
00:20:14,089 --> 00:20:15,890
I am the Princess Snow White.

488
00:20:15,924 --> 00:20:18,092
[laughter]

489
00:20:18,697 --> 00:20:20,226
BOY: I have traveled this land

490
00:20:20,261 --> 00:20:23,063
